Description: NG_001728.3/AF500654.1  missing from assembly
Resolution_Information: AF500654 and AY318212 have their best placements to the same location on build 37 reference and Celera assemblies. AF500654 and AY318212 are mined from two different versions of the Celera assembly. Based on BLAST of Celera trace, AF500654 has best matches to 7 traces from strain A/J and DBA/2J, whereas NG_003367.1 has best matches to 3 traces from strain 129X1/SVJ. No single strain (A/J, DBA/2J, 129X1/SVJ, or C57BL/6) supports two separate loci, so these all appear to be allelic. Consequently, GeneIDs 257840 and 404459 have been merged, and the NG_ was updated based on the reference sequence.

Description: It's unclear if Klra14 is erroneously missing from the reference assembly or validly not present in the C57BL/6 genome. PMID 10528196 states: \It is more probable that the Ly49P gene is simply silent, or missing altogether, in certain strains of mice such as B6. The former possibility is supported by the recent characterization of five additional Ly49 genes in B6 mice (3). Although it has only been partially characterized, the intracellular domain of Ly49L is more closely related to Ly49P than either Ly49A or D. The fact that CBA/J mice also appear to have an activating Ly49A-like molecule (as shown by immunoprecipitation studies identical with those done in Fig. 1Go, data not shown) lends support for the theory that Ly49P is, for whatever reason, silenced in B6 mice.\" [landrum]"
